"content": "<style>\nh1.thlex-title { font-size: 1.3em; margin: 0 0 0.4em; }\n.thlex-key { color: #888; font-size: 0.85em; font-weight: normal; margin-right: 0.4em; }\nnav.thlex-index { margin: 0.5em 0 0.75em; }\nnav.thlex-index ul { margin: 0; padding-left: 1.2em; }\nnav.thlex-index li { margin: 0.15em 0; font-size: 0.95em; }\n.thlex-section { margin: 0.6em 0; }\nh2.thlex-heading { font-size: 1em; margin: 0.5em 0 0.2em; }\nh3.thlex-subheading { font-size: 0.95em; font-weight: normal; font-style: italic; margin: 0.2em 0; }\n.thlex-language-sets { margin: 0.3em 0 0.3em 1em; }\n.thlex-language-set { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 0.75em; border-left: 3px solid #e0e0e0; }\n.thlex-language { font-size: 0.8em; color: #888; margin-right: 0.4em; }\n.thlex-lemma { font-weight: bold; font-family: serif; }\n.thlex-translit { color: #555; font-style: italic; font-size: 0.9em; margin-left: 0.3em; }\n.thlex-refs { font-size: 0.85em; color: #444; margin-top: 0.15em; }\n.thlex-paragraphs p { margin: 0.35em 0; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.5; }\n.thlex-image { margin: 0.5em 0; display: block; }\n.thlex-image img { max-width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; }\nfigcaption.thlex-caption { font-size: 0.85em; color: #555; font-style: italic; margin-top: 0.2em; }\n.thlex-abbr { border-bottom: 1px dotted #888; cursor: help; }\n.thlex-xref { color: #1a5fb4; }\nspan[data-bnType=\"bibleReference\"] { color: #1a5fb4; }\ntable.thlex-table { border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 0.9em; margin: 0.5em 0; }\ntable.thlex-table td { padding: 0.2em 0.6em; vertical-align: top; border: 1px solid #ddd; }\ntable.thlex-table tr:first-child td { font-weight: bold; background: #f5f5f5; }\nul.thlex-index-list { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.6; }\nul.thlex-index-list ul { margin: 0.1em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; }\n.thlex-index-key { font-weight: bold; font-style: italic; }\n</style><h1 class=\"thlex-title\" id=\"REALIA:7.4.2\"><span class=\"thlex-key\">7.4.2</span> Cymbals</h1><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">References:</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-sets\">\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">מְצִלְתַּיִם</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(mtsiltayim)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr13:8\">1CH 13:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr15:16\">1CH 15:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr15:19\">1CH 15:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr15:28\">1CH 15:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr16:5\">1CH 16:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr16:42\">1CH 16:42</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr25:1\">1CH 25:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr25:6\">1CH 25:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr5:12\">2CH 5:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr5:13\">2CH 5:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr29:25\">2CH 29:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra3:10\">EZR 3:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh12:27\">NEH 12:27</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">צֶלְצְלִים</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(tseltselim)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam6:5\">2SA 6:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps150:5\">PSA 150:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps150:5\">PSA 150:5</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">κύμβαλον</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(kumbalon)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor13:1\">1CO 13:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jdt16:1\">JDT 16:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Macc4:54\">1MA 4:54</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Macc13:51\">1MA 13:51</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Esd5:57\">1ES 5:57</a></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">Description:</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>\n            <figure class=\"thlex-image\"><img class=\"thlex-img\" src=\"images/WEB-0514_cymbals.jpg\" alt=\"Cymbals\"><figcaption class=\"thlex-caption\">Cymbals (© Finoskov, CC BY-SA 4.0, via Wikimedia Commons)</figcaption></figure>Cymbals were a percussion instrument consisting of two metal discs that were struck together in order to make a shrill, clashing sound. There were two types of cymbals: (1) flat metal plates that were struck together, and (2) metal cones, one of which was brought down on top of the other, on the open end.</p>\n<hr/>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">Translation:</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>The equivalent of “cymbal” in many languages is a phrase such as “loud metal.”</p>\n<p>In <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps150:5\">PSA 150:5</a> two kinds of cymbals are mentioned, literally “cymbals of hearing” and “cymbals of shouting.” This may mean “small cymbals … large cymbals, or it may be just a poetic variation with the meaning “clanging cymbals … clashing cymbals.”</p>\n<p>In <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor13:1\">1CO 13:1</a><abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Good News Translation (1992)\">GNT</abbr> renders the Greek word <em>kumbalon</em> as “bell” instead of “cymbal” since it is more widely understood.</p>\n</div>\n</div>",
